e-jesus tag-love-like-jesus tag-neighbors tag-sam-riviera entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/getting-to-know-our-neighbors/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="230" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/houses-neighbors-neighborhood1-340x230.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="How to Get to Know Your Neighbors" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/getting-to-know-our-neighbors/">How to Get to Know Your Neighbors</a></h2></header></article><article class="post-16244 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-featured category-redeeming-church category-redeeming-life tag-discipleship tag-evangelism tag-homeless tag-looks-like-jesus tag-love-like-jesus tag-ministry tag-missions tag-poor tag-sam-riviera tag-theology-church entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/how-to-help-homeless-people/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="230" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/homeless-people1-340x230.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="How You Can Help Homeless People" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/how-to-help-homeless-people/">How You Can Help Homeless People</a></h2></header></article><article class="post-12396 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-featured tag-fishing-for-men entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/adventures-in-fishing-for-men/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="230" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/fishing-for-men1-340x230.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Adventures in Fishing (for Men)" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/adventures-in-fishing-for-men/">Adventures in Fishing (for Men)</a></h2></header></article><article class="post-11588 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-featured category-redeeming-theology tag-adultery tag-blasphemy-against-the-holy-spirit tag-divorce tag-forgiveness tag-grace tag-matthew-1231-32 tag-mercy tag-murder tag-sin tag-unforgivable-sin tag-unpardonable-sin entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/unforgivable-sin/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="230" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/unforgivable-sin-340x230.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Are you afraid of the Unforgivable Sin? Don&#8217;t be. You have NOT committed it!" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/unforgivable-sin/">Are you afraid of the Unforgivable Sin? Don&#8217;t be. You have NOT committed it!</a></h2></header></article><article class="post-5766 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-featured category-redeeming-scripture tag-bibliology tag-inerrancy tag-inspiration tag-scripture tag-theology-bible entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/bibliology-is-dangerous/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="230" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Bibliology-2-570x427-1-340x230.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Bibliology is Dangerous" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/bibliology-is-dangerous/">Bibliology is Dangerous</a></h2></header></article></div></section><section id="text-4" class="widget widget_text"><div class="widget-wrap"><div class="textwidget"><h2 style="text-align: center; font-size:5rem;">Recent Blog Posts</h2></div></div></section><section id="featured-post-2" class="widget featured-content featuredpost"><div class="widget-wrap"><article class="post-47517 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-one-verse category-redeeming-church category-redeeming-scripture category-z tag-baptism tag-baptized tag-bible-teaching tag-disciple tag-discipleship tag-follow-jesus tag-matthew-2819-20 entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/matthew-28-19-20/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="140" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Baptism-1-340x140.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="1 crazy suggestion about Matthew 28:19-20 that just might solve the baptism debate" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/matthew-28-19-20/">1 crazy suggestion about Matthew 28:19-20 that just might solve the baptism debate</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>When you were baptized, what words were said? Do you remember? Some people look to Matthew 28:19-20 as the proper words for baptism, while others look to the practice of the Apostles in Acts. In this post, I dispel this entire baptism debate with one crazy suggestion. Read it and let me know what you think!</p></div></article><article class="post-47510 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-redeeming-books tag-books-im-reading tag-wisdom entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/seek-wisdom/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="333" height="140" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wisdom-books-333x140.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Seek Wisdom above all else &#8230; and read this book to help" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/seek-wisdom/">Seek Wisdom above all else &#8230; and read this book to help</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>We all want to be wise &#8230; and the wisdom books are God&#8217;s divinely inspired wisdom for how to live life in His world. In other words, when it comes to wisdom for life, there is no better source than the wisdom books of the Bible.</p></div></article><article class="post-47506 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-redeeming-books tag-apologetics tag-bible-and-theology-questions tag-books-im-reading entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/christianity-is-reasonable/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="140" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/questions-340x140.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Christianity IS Reasonable &#8230; So Don&#8217;t Be Afraid of the Questions" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/christianity-is-reasonable/">Christianity IS Reasonable &#8230; So Don&#8217;t Be Afraid of the Questions</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>Evidence that Demands a Verdict not only provides a good basis for helping us know how we can trust that the Bible we have today is the Bible that was written by the original authors, but also shows how we can trust the historical claims of the Bible.</p></div></article><article class="post-47483 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-one-verse category-redeeming-scripture category-z tag-1-peter-321 tag-baptism tag-baptized tag-salvation tag-save entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/baptism-1-peter-3-21/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="140" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/baptism-1-Peter-3-21-340x140.jpg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Does baptism save us? (1 Peter 3:21)" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/baptism-1-peter-3-21/">Does baptism save us? (1 Peter 3:21)</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>In 1 Peter 3:21, it appears that Peter is saying that we must be baptized in order to be saved. He writes that baptism saves us. But if this is true, then how is eternal life by faith alone and not of works?</p></div></article><article class="post-47453 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-one-verse category-redeeming-scripture tag-1-corinthians-927 tag-approved tag-crown tag-disqualified tag-eternal-life tag-eternal-rewards tag-eternal-security tag-gospel-dictionary entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/1-corinthians-9-27-disqualified/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="140" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Disqualified-340x140.png" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Does 1 Corinthians 9:27 teach that you can lose your salvation?" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/1-corinthians-9-27-disqualified/">Does 1 Corinthians 9:27 teach that you can lose your salvation?</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>First Corinthians 9:27 is sometimes quoted to show that not even Paul was certain that he would go to heaven when he died. Paul writes that he keeps close watch over his body so that he does not end up disqualified (adokimos). So what does this verse mean?</p></div></article><article class="post-47460 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail category-one-verse category-redeeming-theology tag-church tag-inerrancy tag-jason-wiedel entry"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/interview-jason-wiedel/" class="aligncenter" aria-hidden="true"><img width="340" height="140" src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Jason-Wiedel-340x140.jpeg" class="entry-image attachment-post" alt="Once upon a time, I was interviewed by Jason Wiedel" itemprop="image" /></a><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title" itemprop="headline"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/interview-jason-wiedel/">Once upon a time, I was interviewed by Jason Wiedel</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>Several years ago, I was interviewed by Jason Wiedel for his podcast. For some reason, he never aired this interview. I don&#8217;t know why. But I am airing it now. Enjoy!</p></div></article></div></section><section id="text-28" class="widget widget_text"><div class="widget-wrap"><div class="textwidget"><a href="http://redeeminggod.com/archives/"><img src="https://redeeminggod.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/blog-post-banner-1080x450.jpg" alt="RedeemingGod.com archives" width="1080" height="450" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-44171" /></a></div></div></section></div></div></main></div></div></div><div class="footer-widgets"><div class="wrap"><div class="widget-area footer-widgets-1 footer-widget-area"><section id="nav_menu-2" class="widget widget_nav_menu"><div class="widget-wrap"><h4 class="widget-title widgettitle">Theological Study Archives</h4><div class="menu-theology-container"><ul id="menu-theology" class="menu"><li id="menu-item-38253" class="menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-38253"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/bible-theology-topics/theology-general/" itemprop="url">Theology &#8211; General</a></li><li id="menu-item-38238" class="menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-38238"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/bible-theology-topics/theology-intro/" itemprop="url">Theology Introduction</a></li><li id="menu-item-38245" class="menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-38245"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/bible-theology-topics/theology-bible/" itemprop="url">Theology of the Bible</a></li><li id="menu-item-38240" class="menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-38240"><a href="https://redeeminggod.com/bible-theology-topics/theology-study